const medViability = ideas.filter(i => i.viability === 'medium').length

const papers = [
  { short: "Paper 1", title: "The Observer-Centric Action and Self-Dual A₅ Geometry", date: "Oct 2025" },
  { short: "Paper 2", title: "Neutrino Flavor Structure from Icosahedral–Dodecahedral Geometry", date: "Nov 2025" },
  { short: "Paper 3", title: "Complementarity and Coherence Conservation in Observer-Centrism", date: "Oct 2025" },
  { short: "Paper 4", title: "Informational Plateau Equivalence and the Conservation of Coherence Flow", date: "Nov 2025" },
]
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '')
---

<MainLayout title="Extension Papers Analysis">
  <PageTitle title="Extension Papers: Idea Analysis" />
  <p>
    Alongside the main whitepaper, four extension papers explored more speculative directions
    within the earlier Observer-Centrism framework. These papers used the same foundation
    &mdash; the OC action, Fisher information metric, A₅ icosahedral geometry, and functional
    renormalization group &mdash; to address neutrino flavor structure, gauge coupling predictions,
    self-duality, and a complementarity principle.
  </p>
  <p>
    These papers are <strong>more speculative</strong> than the core whitepaper, and their
    results depend heavily on the specific OC action formalism. This analysis catalogs their
    distinct ideas, assesses coverage in the current rigorous framework, and evaluates viability
    for absorption &mdash; judged, as before, by whether an idea is <em>plausibly derivable</em>
    from the current axioms and derivation chain.
  </p>

  <div class="pa-papers">
    <h3>Papers analyzed</h3>
    <ol>
      {papers.map(p => (
        <li><strong>{p.title}</strong> <span class="pa-date">({p.date})</span></li>
      ))}
    </ol>
  </div>

  <div class="wa-summary">
    <div class="wa-stat">
      <div class="wa-stat-value">{ideas.length}</div>
      <div class="wa-stat-label">Ideas cataloged</div>
    </div>
    <div class="wa-stat">
      <div class="wa-stat-value">{covered}</div>
      <div class="wa-stat-label">Already covered</div>
    </div>
    <div class="wa-stat">
      <div class="wa-stat-value">{partial}</div>
      <div class="wa-stat-label">Partially covered</div>
    </div>
    <div class="wa-stat">
      <div class="wa-stat-value">{notCovered}</div>
      <div class="wa-stat-label">Not yet covered</div>
    </div>
    <div class="wa-stat">
      <div class="wa-stat-value">{highViability + medViability}</div>
      <div class="wa-stat-label">High/medium viability</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="pa-note">
    <strong>Key observation:</strong> These papers are significantly more coupled to the
    prior framework's specific formalism (OC action, Fisher metric, A₅ lattice, FRG projectors)
    than the whitepaper's core ideas. Most of the machinery cannot be directly transferred.
    The most promising transferable ideas are in the <strong>flavor physics</strong> domain
    (ideas 5&ndash;11), where the conceptual structure &mdash; geometry-determined flavor breaking,
    discrete residual symmetries, two-sector mixing architecture &mdash; could potentially be
    re-derived using the current framework's winding-axis and bootstrap mechanisms.
  </div>

  {ideas.map(idea => (
    <div class="wa-card" id={`idea-${idea.id}`}>
      <div class="wa-card-header">
        <span class="wa-id">{idea.id}</span>
        <h3 class="wa-name">{idea.name}</h3>
        <div class="wa-badges">
          <span class={`wa-badge ${coverageClass(idea.coverage)}`}>{coverageLabel(idea.coverage)}</span>
          <span class={`wa-badge ${viabilityClass(idea.viability)}`}>{viabilityLabel(idea.viability)}</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="wa-section-ref">{idea.paperRef}</div>
      <p class="wa-description">{idea.description}</p>
      <div class="wa-assessment">
        <div class="wa-assessment-block">
          <h4>Coverage in current framework</h4>
          <p>{idea.coverageNotes}</p>
        </div>
        <div class="wa-assessment-block">
          <h4>Viability for absorption</h4>
          <p>{idea.viabilityNotes}</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  ))}

  <div class="pa-summary-section">
    <h2>Cross-Reference with Whitepaper Analysis</h2>
    <p>
      Several ideas in these papers overlap with or extend ideas already cataloged in earlier analyses. Key connections:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>γV_cτ = ℏ</strong> (idea #13 here, idea #7 in whitepaper) &mdash; same
        invariant, same assessment: already captured by the framework's action-planck derivation.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Coherence conservation hierarchy</strong> (idea #24 here, idea #16 in whitepaper)
        &mdash; already absorbed as Axiom 1 and its consequences.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Gauge symmetry derivation</strong> (ideas #4, #15 here, idea #11 in whitepaper)
        &mdash; deriving gauge dynamics from coherence remains the highest-priority open extension.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Coupling constants</strong> (ideas #17, #22 here, idea #28 in whitepaper)
        &mdash; remains an open problem; the OC pipeline is too formalism-dependent to transfer.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Flavor physics</strong> (ideas #5&ndash;11 here, new) &mdash; the most
        distinctive contribution of these papers, with moderate viability for absorption
        via the winding-axis mechanism.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</MainLayout>

<style>
  .pa-papers {
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
    margin: 1.25rem 0;
  }
  .pa-papers h3 {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    border: none;
    padding: 0;
  }
  .pa-papers ol {
    margin: 0;
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }
  .pa-date {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    font-size: 0.8rem;
  }

  .pa-note {
    background: #fffbeb;
    border: 1px solid #fbbf24;
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
    margin: 1.25rem 0;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .pa-summary-section {
    margin-top: 2rem;
    padding-top: 1.5rem;
    border-top: 2px solid var(--color-border);
  }
  .pa-summary-section h2 {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
  .pa-summary-section ul {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
  }

  .wa-summary {
    display: flex;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    margin: 1.5rem 0 2rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }
  .wa-stat {
    flex: 1;
    min-width: 100px;
    padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 8px;
    text-align: center;
  }
  .wa-stat-label {
    font-size: 0.65rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
  }
  .wa-stat-value {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  .wa-card {
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 1.25rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    background: var(--color-surface);
  }
  .wa-card-header {
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }
  .wa-id {
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    background: var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 9999px;
    width: 1.5rem;
    height: 1.5rem;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    margin-top: 0.1rem;
  }
  .wa-name {
    flex: 1;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin: 0;
    min-width: 200px;
    border: none;
    padding: 0;
  }
  .wa-badges {
    display: flex;
    gap: 0.4rem;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }
  .wa-badge {
    font-size: 0.65rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    padding: 0.15rem 0.5rem;
    border-radius: 9999px;
    letter-spacing: 0.03em;
    white-space: nowrap;
  }
  .wa-cov-covered { background: #dcfce7; color: #166534; }
  .wa-cov-partial { background: #fef3c7; color: #92400e; }
  .wa-cov-not-covered { background: #f3f4f6; color: #6b7280; }
  .wa-via-high { background: #dbeafe; color: #1e40af; }
  .wa-via-medium { background: #e0e7ff; color: #4338ca; }
  .wa-via-low { background: #f3f4f6; color: #6b7280; }
  .wa-via-not-viable { background: #fef2f2; color: #991b1b; }

  .wa-section-ref {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    margin-left: 2.25rem;
  }
  .wa-description {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }
  .wa-assessment {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }
  @media (max-width: 700px) {
    .wa-assessment { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
  .wa-assessment-block {
    background: #fafaf9;
    border-radius: 6px;
    padding: 0.75rem;
  }
  .wa-assessment-block h4 {
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    margin: 0 0 0.35rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.03em;
  }
  .wa-assessment-block p {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    line-height: 1.55;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin: 0;
  }
</style>
